title: LawyerStory1
tags:
position: 169,38
---
Lawyer Ghost: Being a lawyer down here is fascinating.
Lawyer Ghost: Every case down here, such as theft or divorce, has a nicer and more clearcut set of rules than it was when I was alive.
Lawyer Ghost: Hey, I've been meaning to ask you a couple questions. No, I'm not trying to interrogate you about a murder - you would know if I was, and nobody really gets murdered here.
Lawyer Ghost: Have you heard anything about... a dog?
<<emotionChange Sad>>
Lawyer Ghost: Things are kind of hazy, but I remember a storm... did I die in a flood? A hurricane?
<<emotionChange Normal>>
Lawyer Ghost: But I don't really remember the details about my passing, and I just really hope he's alright. I really hope I didn't order a hot chocolate back then - my dog loves to try and steal my drinks.
<<emotionChange Sad>>
Lawyer Ghost: No, it couldn't be a hurricane - I would've known about it a week in advance and left... right?
<<emotionChange Normal>>
Lawyer Ghost: I... I need to think more about this. Thank you for your time.
<<setCam "Main Camera">>
===

title: LawyerStory2
tags:
position: 169,38
---
Lawyer Ghost: Is there really a point to being a lawyer here?
Lawyer Ghost: I've seen bankers switch to partying and partygoers switch to business... maybe I can just go hide in the corner where nobody will even dare look at me.
<<emotionChange Sad>>
Lawyer Ghost: So many ghosts were wronged by society and the court, and I'm probably just their living embodiment of regret... but I digress.
Lawyer Ghost: ...You know you're the only ghost that looks at me in the eye? The rest of them think I'm going to persecute them in court or interrogate them for a crime or even... take a bribe??
Lawyer Ghost: I've been thinking a lot about my previous life. I'm pretty sure I did die in a hurricane... I was probably so tired and determined to finish the case that I ignored all warnings and stayed.
<<emotionChange None Scribbles>>
Lawyer Ghost: Maybe if I was more efficient at my casework, I could have heeded the warning before?
Lawyer Ghost: The only thing I have left is my life's work, and honestly, I should be content with just that.
<<emotionChange None None>>
Lawyer Ghost: But my poor, poor dog... He was just a little pup who wanted love.
Lawyer Ghost: I loved him, I did... I just couldn't love or take care of myself.
Lawyer Ghost: Others didn't see me for me and saw the reflection of society, so I poured my self-worth into my work... but at what cost?
Lawyer Ghost: I need to find my dog.
<<emotionChange Normal>>
Lawyer Ghost: Please tell me if you find him. Thank you for your time.
<<setCam "Main Camera">>
===

title: LawyerStory3
tags:
position: 169,38
---
Lawyer Ghost: I finally found my boy... or Dog Ghost, as he goes by now.
<<emotionChange Sad>>
Lawyer Ghost: He told me that he just waited for me to come back from the tree falling on me, and when he realized I was gone... he just sat by my body and curled up next to me until he passed, too.
Lawyer Ghost: I... don't think I can ever forgive myself for leaving him like that.
<<emotionChange Normal>>
Lawyer Ghost: But you know what?
Lawyer Ghost: In all of my self-deprecation and prejudice, I found that it's okay and almost necessary to rely on others.
Lawyer Ghost: My mistakes are a part of my journey, and  I need to love myself first before I can love others.
Lawyer Ghost: I think I'm going to take a break from the lawyer stuff for a bit to work on myself.
Lawyer Ghost: Well, before I self-reflect some more, I need to meet Dog Ghost for a cup of mocha - ironically, he loves chocolate.
Lawyer Ghost: Thanks for your time.
<<setCam "Main Camera">>
===

title: LawyerStory4
